Hello there!

I'm Kshitij Ambilduke

I recently finished my bachelors in Electronics and Communication Engineering at Visvesvaraya National Institute of Technology (VNIT), India. I am currently working in the SARDINE group as a Trainee Researcher at the Instituto de Telecomunicaes, Lisbon.

Previously, I pursued a research internship co-advised by Dr. Andre Martins and Dr. Bruno Martins at Instituto Superior Tcnico, Lisbon where worked on Visual Question answering. I am interested in Deep Learning and Natural Language Processing and I'm particularly fascinated by the challenges lying in the intersection of language with other modalities.

Besides this, I play badminton, cricket, and Valorant and spend my time listening to pop music.

Here's a big thumbs up for visiting me : )

Projects

For a more detailed description, please refer to the projects page

Enhancing context through contrast

We proposed an additional novel pre-training step based on Barlow twins contrastive loss for Neural Machine Translation.

Medical Visual Question answering

Reviewed & compiled notes on several research papers on VQA and implemented several Medical VQA baselines using Meta AI's MMF framework

Neural Machine Translation

Implemented several NMT models from scratch in PyTorch including SOTA models like Transformers

Language Modelling

Implemented several word and character level language models like RNN, LSTM & GRU in PyTorch.

Image Captioning

Studied and implemented several image captioning models using PyTorch. Further, wrote a review paper on the basis of the studies model.

Visual Transformers

Reviewed several works on transformer-based vision models and implemented Visual Transformers from scratch in PyTorch.

Memes-vs-notes

Trained and tested DNNs and CNNs, built from scratch in NumPy and PyTorch respectively, on a custom Memes-vs-notes dataset.
